# Tailwind CSS Styling Rule

All visual styling MUST use Tailwind CSS utility classes via the `className` prop.

## Prohibited

- `style={{ ... }}` inline style objects
- CSS-in-JS (emotion, styled-components, etc.)
- Separate `.css` / `.scss` module files for component-level styles (global `index.css` is fine)

## Required

- Use Tailwind utility classes: `className="flex items-center gap-2 p-3 rounded-lg"`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge conditional classes
- Dynamic values → Tailwind arbitrary values: `className="w-[180px] min-h-[140px]"`
- Theme colors → CSS variable classes: `text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `border-border`

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div style={{ padding: 8, background: '#fff', borderRadius: 8 }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="p-2 bg-background rounded-lg">
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<span style={{ fontSize: 12, color: selected ? '#6366f1' : '#e2e8f0' }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<span className={cn("text-xs", selected ? "text-indigo-400" : "text-border")}>
```
